description.plain:
Dan + Shay is a country music duo made up of vocalists/songwriters Dan Smyers and Shay Mooney.  They met at a party at Shay’s home on December 7, 2012.  They are known for “Nothin' Like You” and “19 You + Me.”

Daniel Smyers was born August 16, 1987.  He was raised in Wexford, Pennsylvania.  He attended North Allegheny Senior High School in Wexford, PA and studied Finance at Carnegie Mellon University.  The singer/songwriter currently resides in Nashville.

Dan + Shay went on to win the “Vocal Duo of the Year”  award at the 53rd CMA Awards.

songs.title: Speechless

description.plain:
“Speechless” is country duo Dan + Shay’s first song to hit number 1 on the Billboard Country chart.

It describes the scene of a wedding, and the groom’s delight at the beauty of the bride.
It is also about not getting used to your partner’s beauty. After all the time they have been together, he still is surprised and amazed with her beauty.

songs.title: Tequila

description.plain: “Tequila” is country duo Dan + Shay’s 2018 hit song detailing flashbacks of a lost relationship induced exclusively by tequila. The song reached the number 2 spot on the Billboard Country chart, and 21 on the main chart.

description.plain:
Nearly eight months into 2020, “I Should Probably Go To Bed” marks Dan + Shay’s first song of the year. The track follows the duo’s hit success on the Justin Bieber-assisted “10,000 Hours” and should appear on their fourth studio album, DS4*.

At large, the lyrics describe an event in which one is tempted to reconnect with an ex-lover after they return home. It’s ultimately revealed that this is a poor choice and that the individual should “probably go to bed” instead.
